PRIORITY 0: CRITICAL BUGS FIXED (this session)
========================================================================

1. PIO TYPE MISMATCH IN MPAS REMAP WRITE [DONE]
   [x] Root cause of ALL 171+ remapped MPAS issues identified:
       pio_initdecomp(PIO_REAL) = float32 decomposition, but
       pio_write_darray received real(r8) = float64 data.
       PIO reads 4-byte chunks from 8-byte elements → interleaved
       valid/garbage values in output.
   [x] Fixed: convert fld_out to real(4) before pio_write_darray in
       mpas_ocn_fme_horiz_remap.F and mpas_seaice_fme_horiz_remap.F.
   [x] Lesson: PIO decomposition type MUST match Fortran array type.
       No runtime error when mismatched — silent data corruption.

2. EAM FILL THRESHOLD TOO HIGH [DONE]
   [x] fill_thresh was 1e30 but cam_history fillvalue is 1e20.
       The 1e20 values from vcoarsen (high-elevation columns) leaked
       through SpMV, producing T_1..T_8 min values of 37-110K.
   [x] Fixed: fill_thresh lowered to 1e10 in horiz_remap_mod.F90.

3. MPAS FILL VALUE LEAKAGE THROUGH SpMV [DONE]
   [x] Depth-coarsened fields have 1e34 fill at deep levels for
       shallow ocean cells. Added abs > 1e10 zeroing in MPAS-O and
       MPAS-SI send buffer packing.

